{"id":"d=origam-topic-3701//p=374cb521dc6f4bceb965f6c57903f12b","tags":{"__document_id":["origam-topic-3701"],"__file_type":["text/plain"],"__file_id":["faa036e75fd048a6b5eef0cbf1efb8f0"],"__file_part":["7a1ea939145f4e1985a32f2cf7f3db25"],"__part_n":["0"],"__sect_n":["0"],"source":["origam-community"],"topicId":["3701"],"categoryId":["61"],"url":["https://community.origam.com/t/5-work-environment/3701"],"title":["5. Work environment"],"imagesFound":["8"],"imagesDescribed":["8"],"imageUrl":["https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/2/2a0d745b5d588156a99d6a8524e556fda381964f.jpeg","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/f/f000e530aba40609e79fdd8b04d814c6300c02f5.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/8/82a800ba005ad6340d5ebfa4d5155d6d7b9200dc.jpeg","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/8/80c52e08febca366bc999d68b547ed314825e5fb.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/8/8e5cb4daea457b5a88ffa5c8ebf0578e0d43278e.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/c/c127b222fce6f687eac5bf648e72bf0fe8fbfd9d.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/b/bc38230577c3ba6f5ed6aac8a151eeb1d9bc91a4.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/e/e7906fefbdd5b9ffc77ec700f2d78eb5e5ecdc74.png"]},"payload":{"url":"","schema":"20231218A","file":"content.txt","text":"# 5. Work environment\n\nURL: https://community.origam.com/t/5-work-environment/3701\n\n@vikter (2025-01-24 14:19:42Z):\n   \n \n   This article helps you get a basic orientation of the two main components of the ORIGAM Platform: the Architect and the client application. This serves as preparation for creating your own project and application. \n \n \n    New here?  If you haven\u2019t installed and set up the ORIGAM Architect yet, please refer to the previous chapter:  Getting Ready . \n \n   The ORIGAM Architect \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/2/2a0d745b5d588156a99d6a8524e556fda381964f.jpeg]\nDescription: The image depicts the ORIGAM Architect interface for model management, specifically highlighting the database field properties. The top section features navigation elements labeled \u0022Document,\u0022 \u0022Tools,\u0022 and \u0022New\u0022 for task creation and filtering options, including \u0022Create Lookup Field,\u0022 \u0022Create Filter,\u0022 and \u0022Dynamic Field Label.\u0022 The main area displays details for the database field titled \u0022Name,\u0022 under which various attributes are listed such as \u0022AllowNulls,\u0022 \u0022DataLength,\u0022 and \u0022String.\u0022 The sidebar on the right, labeled \u0022Model Browser,\u0022 outlines project components, including \u0022Common,\u0022 \u0022Data,\u0022 \u0022Entities,\u0022 and specific details on \u0022myproject.\u0022 A description for the \u0022Name\u0022 attribute indicates its role in model identification. A search bar is present at the top, facilitating quick navigation within the model.\n\n\n  \n The Architect consists of the following parts: \n  1: Upper bar  \n   \n The upper bar displays the name of your open project, the name of the currently open package within the project, and its model version. \n A package is a functionality bundle that forms part of the model. When you open a new project, you will notice that several default packages are already created, such as Root, Root Menu, and Security. These packages contain the basic functionality required by any application. Unless you\u2019re building something like your own login infrastructure, you\u2019ll typically use these and add new packages to provide your own functionality on top of them. \n  2: Main menu  \n Here, you will find all the available functions and settings in one place, organized into categories. \n   \n  3: Toolbar  \n This is another menu offering a selection of functions divided into four sections: Document, Tools, Actions, and New. The first two sections are fixed, while the rest change depending on the context. \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/f/f000e530aba40609e79fdd8b04d814c6300c02f5.png]\nDescription: The image displays a user interface for a document management or data manipulation application. It includes a toolbar with several sections: \u0022Document\u0022 and \u0022Tools\u0022 sections. Within the \u0022Document\u0022 section, options include \u0022Save,\u0022 \u0022Refresh,\u0022 and \u0022Finish Task.\u0022 The \u0022Tools\u0022 section features options labeled \u0022Restart Server(s),\u0022 \u0022Create Lookup Field (incl. entity),\u0022 \u0022Create Relationship with key,\u0022 \u0022Create (=) Filter,\u0022 \u0022Create (=) Filter With Parameter,\u0022 and \u0022Create (Like) Filter.\u0022 Additionally, the \u0022Actions\u0022 section allows for \u0022Row Level Security Rule,\u0022 \u0022Dependency,\u0022 and \u0022Dynamic Field Label.\u0022 The apparent purpose of this interface is to facilitate data management and configuration tasks.\n\n\n  \n  4: Editor tab bar  \n The tab bar displays all the open editors, such as data entities or tools like the SQL generator. \n   \n  5: Editor  \n This is the main workspace, where you can edit data elements, user interfaces, workflows, business logic, and more. \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/8/82a800ba005ad6340d5ebfa4d5155d6d7b9200dc.jpeg]\nDescription: The image presents a user interface for a database field configuration, labeled \u0022Database Field: Name.\u0022 It features multiple sections: \n\n1. **(Info)** with fields including Id (bce04b2d-7631-40f9-98d6-5f6b31fd46eb), ItemType (DataEntityColumn), PackageName (myproject), RelativeFilePath (myproject\\DataEntity\\myproject\\Project.origa), and SchemaItemType (Origam.Schema.EntityModel.FieldMappingItem).\n2. **(Schema Item)** indicating properties such as Inheritable (False) and Name (Name).\n3. **Entity Column** attributes detailing AllowNulls (False), AutoIncrement (False), Caption (Name), DataLength (50), DataType (String), and several other boolean flags set to False.\n4. ","vector_provider":"AI.Ollama.OllamaTextEmbeddingGenerator","vector_generator":"__","last_update":"2026-05-01T23:35:23"},"vector":[0.0058091315,0.000851048,-0.075987,0.012568336,-0.003579245,-0.049461525,-0.026836853,-0.0078524165,0.01566563,0.015632058,0.008223333,-0.03206866,-0.0008888136,0.009902939,0.010741172,-0.010079054,0.0139594115,0.032228637,0.042999126,0.035932142,-0.0087458845,0.0037889688,0.029040812,0.018479634,-0.013831938,0.0307069,-0.020137154,-0.03982834,-0.007734064,0.021381926,0.0058952994,-0.076394126,-0.002055033,0.0046375203,-0.010440065,-0.018614667,0.018920165,-0.012363125,-0.041888528,0.03414471,-0.028280739,-0.0023200023,-0.0052845953,0.0049176496,0.0018827161,-0.050363224,-0.009126021,-0.0065033366,-0.0026239192,-0.03909713,-0.03153752,-0.044766575,-0.010145293,-0.045862593,0.05396806,0.031803496,-0.059134528,-0.018720485,-0.076475695,0.03313102,-0.040825266,0.014724551,0.016620485,-0.03326076,0.009066489,0.02296596,-0.02926043,0.0064146486,-0.022445241,-0.03725313,-0.006494063,0.014041155,-0.07397747,-0.032706212,-0.07186224,-0.011749797,0.023791738,0.0052092234,-0.064812005,0.016379096,-0.029160954,0.011999177,0.043496072,-0.036186233,-0.010637102,0.0074927066,-0.05065487,0.07434245,0.012059398,0.025902292,-0.03705086,-0.040273026,0.066378765,-0.047365863,-0.035140187,0.0011850927,-0.0039019808,-0.008642532,0.014450063,0.02136808,-0.04997633,-0.022386963,-0.031320535,0.024615776,-0.0038248964,-0.029822694,0.02694233,-0.022268858,0.0066521163,-0.05038008,0.0020142437,-0.0040717125,0.05533715,0.00032887998,0.0012405195,-0.026277902,0.006487011,-0.028501399,-0.008276453,-0.0012118949,0.016829064,0.009855092,0.0880723,-0.018300463,-0.0047511472,-0.010400433,0.0014086574,0.0362396,-0.011384355,0.022478577,0.03972167,-0.008770726,-0.034506936,-0.0048717926,-0.012614163,-0.